column1: #Text=Russian government homosexuality position leads to NYC Russian vodka boycott
#Text=As of Monday , over 200 New York City area bars and restaurants had committed to boycotting Russian vodka in response to anti- homosexuality related laws passed by the country 's government .

#Text=The boycott follows another event that took place on Monday where bottles of vodka were poured onto the streets of the city , as part of a protest by the President of United Restaurant and Tavern Owners Association , Paul Hurley .

#Text=New York One quotes Hurley as saying the reason for the boycott as , " We 're not stupid , we 're reading papers , we 're reading what 's going on over there , they 've got to stop what 's happened . "
#Text=The press conference announcing the New York City boycott took place at Desmonds Steakhouse located on the 38th Street and 7th Avenue .
#Text=LGBT activists and models attended the event .
#Text=Johnny Donovan , manager of J Donovan Productions , is quoted by the New York Daily Times as saying , " Shame on Russia ! [ ... ]
